Airtel Nigeria has been named among the top three most compliant tax payers in Nigeria and has also been recognised for its remarkable performance in remittances of the various taxes in 2021. Airtel was recognised by the Federal Inland Revenue Service (FIRS) during the agency’s second edition of its stakeholder engagement forum held at the Banquet Hall, State House Presidential Villa, Abuja.   NIN-SIM linkage: Queues continue at enrolment centres,…     Zenith Bank gives N93.33b dividends     CBN fines four banks over crypto transactions   Airtel Nigeria’s Vice President, Finance, Adenike Ayeye and Head, Taxation, Mary Okoro, received the award for the company at the event which was attended by President Muhammadu Buhari. Minister of Finance, Budget and National Planning, Zainab Ahmed, said the forum was designed to engage stakeholders in the tax-space in a discourse to glean information, ideas and experience to aid policy formulation and improved tax environment.